title: Grateful Dead Live at Nassau Coliseum on 1979-11-01
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw, They Love Each Other, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, Peggy-O, Minglewood Blues, Candyman, Looks Like Rain, Don't Ease Me In, Easy To Love You, Promised Land

Set 2

Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Samson & Delilah, Terrapin Station-> Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> Black Peter-> Good Lovin', E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: How Can You Not? Thanks J for another fine upload.  Sound on this is just what you want in a Matrix.  Clarity and Fullness.  You are there, but you can also hear every instrument, Phil especially who is on fire this night.  As for the performance, I don't think I can add much that hasn't already been said. S>F is a beast, despite a few moments I wish they had turned Brent's Casio 1000 Plink-O-Matic way down, or off completely. A standout show from a standout tour.   Additional note to the individual who says we hand out too many 5 star ratings: Lighten Up Francis; it's all personal opinion.
brent playing in the band..just great dead....drums are recorded and played well....the keyboard here is just nuts....then the whale sounds...omg....what a show
Breath of fresh air Brent was such an inspiration for this band, after a year and half of Keith's end.  Love the jams, tons of great ones in this show.
